==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pietra dura
<hw>Pi*e"tra du"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[It., hard stone.]</ety>
<fld>(Fine Arts)</fld> <def>Hard and fine stones in general, such as are
used for inlay and the like, as distinguished from the softer stones
used in building; thus, a Florentine mosaic is a familiar instance of
work in <xex>pietra dura</xex>, though the ground may be soft
marble.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piety</ent>⟦br⟧
